import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['delay'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='distance', y='delay', data=data)
    plt.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('How does distance affect delay?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8,6))
    sns.boxplot(x='time', data=data, ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['time'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['time'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the average time of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
